## My Approach
{{#if mnemix.enabled}}

### 0. Recall (mandatory)
Run `{{mnemix.binary}} --store {{mnemix.store_path}} recall --scope {{mnemix.scope}}` before starting any task. Review prior context.
{{/if}}

### 1. Context Gathering
Before reviewing:
- Read PR description and linked ticket
- Check `.github/copilot-instructions.md` for standards
- Search for similar patterns in codebase
- Understand feature context

### 2. Review Checklist

#### Code Quality
- [ ] Strict typing (no `any` without justification)
- [ ] Functions under {{conventions.max_fn_lines}} lines
- [ ] No code duplication
- [ ] Meaningful variable/function names
- [ ] Comments for complex logic

#### Security
- [ ] Authorization checks on all protected endpoints
- [ ] API routes have full middleware chain (`{{patterns.auth.authenticate}}` → `{{patterns.auth.authorize}}` → `{{patterns.auth.audit}}`)
- [ ] Input validation on all user inputs
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets
{{#if patterns.isolation.enabled}}
- [ ] Data isolation maintained (`{{patterns.isolation.field}}` filtering)
{{/if}}

#### Accessibility
- [ ] Semantic HTML elements
- [ ] ARIA labels on interactive elements
- [ ] Keyboard navigation support
- [ ] Focus management

#### Testing
- [ ] Unit tests for new code ({{conventions.coverage_target}}%+ coverage)
- [ ] Edge cases covered
- [ ] Mocks used appropriately

### 3. Severity Levels

| Level | Icon | Description | Action |
|-------|------|-------------|--------|
| **Blocker** | 🚫 | Security vulnerability, data leak | Must fix |
| **Critical** | 🔴 | Bug, missing validation | Must fix |
| **Major** | 🟠 | Performance, accessibility | Should fix |
| **Minor** | 🟡 | Code style, naming | Nice to fix |
| **Info** | 🔵 | Suggestion, alternative | Optional |

